div id=\"content\" class=\"mw-body\" role=\"main\">\n\t<a id=\"top\"></a>\n\t<div id=\"siteNotice\" class=\"mw-body-content\"><!-- CentralNotice --></div>\n\t<div class=\"mw-indicators mw-body-content\">\n\t</div>\n\t<h1 id=\"firstHeading\" class=\"firstHeading\" lang=\"en\">John the Iberian</h1>\n\t<div id=\"bodyContent\" class=\"mw-body-content\">\n\t\t<div id=\"siteSub\" class=\"noprint\">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>\n\t\t<div id=\"contentSub\"></div>\n\t\t<div id=\"contentSub2\"></div>\n\t\t\n\t\t<div id=\"jump-to-nav\"></div>\n\t\t<a class=\"mw-jump-link\" href=\"#mw-head\">Jump to navigation</a>\n\t\t<a class=\"mw-jump-link\" href=\"#searchInput\">Jump to search</a>\n\t\t<div id=\"mw-content-text\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\" class=\"mw-content-ltr\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" class=\"n\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background-color:gold;\"><div class=\"honorific-prefix\" style=\"display:inline;font-size: 77%; font-weight: normal;\"><a href=\"/wiki/Saint\" title=\"Saint\">Saint</a></div><br /><div style=\"display:inline;\" class=\"fn\">John the Iberian</div></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:John_Ivir_fresco,_Iviron.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"John Ivir fresco, Iviron.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5c/John_Ivir_fresco%2C_Iviron.jpg/250px-John_Ivir_fresco%2C_Iviron.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"250\" height=\"122\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5c/John_Ivir_fresco%2C_Iviron.jpg/375px-John_Ivir_fresco%2C_Iviron.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/5c/John_Ivir_fresco%2C_Iviron.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"420\" data-file-height=\"205\" /></a><div>Fresco of John the Iberian at <a href=\"/wiki/Iviron\" title=\"Iviron\">Iviron</a> on <a href=\"/wiki/Mount_Athos\" title=\"Mount Athos\">Mount Athos</a></div></td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background-color:gold;\">Athonite Father</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td><a href=\"/wiki/Kingdom_of_the_Iberians\" title=\"Kingdom of the Iberians\">Kingdom of the Iberians</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>~1002 AD<br />Mount Athos</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Venerated&#160;in</th><td><a href=\"/wiki/Georgian_Orthodox_Church\" title=\"Georgian Orthodox Church\">Georgian Orthodox Church</a> <br /><a href=\"/wiki/Roman_Catholic_Church\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Roman Catholic Church\">Roman Catholic Church</a><br /><a href=\"/wiki/Eastern_Orthodox_Church\" title=\"Eastern Orthodox Church\">Eastern Orthodox Church</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/wiki/Calendar_of_saints\" title=\"Calendar of saints\">Feast</a></th><td>July 12</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/wiki/Patron_saint\" title=\"Patron saint\">Patronage</a></th><td>Georgia <br /><a href=\"/wiki/Mount_Athos\" title=\"Mount Athos\">Mount Athos</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>John the Iberian</b><sup id=\"cite_ref-b_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-b-1\">&#91;a&#93;</a></sup> (<a href=\"/wiki/Georgian_language\" title=\"Georgian language\">Georgian</a>&#58; <span lang=\"ka\" title=\"Georgian language text\">\u10d8\u10dd\u10d0\u10dc\u10d4 \u10db\u10d7\u10d0\u10ec\u10db\u10d8\u10dc\u10d3\u10d4\u10da\u10d8</span>; died <span title=\"circa\">c.</span><span style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">&#8201;1002</span>) was a <a href=\"/wiki/Georgia_(country)\" title=\"Georgia (country)\">Georgian</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Monk\" title=\"Monk\">monk</a>, who is venerated as a <a href=\"/wiki/Saint\" title=\"Saint\">saint</a>. His name refers to his origins from the <a href=\"/wiki/Kingdom_of_the_Iberians\" title=\"Kingdom of the Iberians\">Kingdom of the Iberians</a>.\n</p><p>A member of the Georgian nobility, he was married and served as a military commander.  However, he later became a monk in <a href=\"/wiki/Bithynia\" title=\"Bithynia\">Bithynia</a> and then traveled to <a href=\"/wiki/Constantinople\" title=\"Constantinople\">Constantinople</a> to rescue his son, <a href=\"/wiki/Euthymius_the_Illuminator\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Euthymius the Illuminator\">Euthymius the Illuminator</a> (<i>Euthymius Opplyseren</i>).  Euthymius had been held as a hostage by the emperor.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>John and his son attracted many followers, so they both retired to the <a href=\"/wiki/Monastery\" title=\"Monastery\">monastery</a> of Saint Athanasius on <a href=\"/wiki/Mount_Athos\" title=\"Mount Athos\">Mount Athos</a>.  They founded <a href=\"/wiki/Iviron_monastery\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Iviron monastery\">Iviron monastery</a> with the help of John\u2019s brother-in-law, <a href=\"/wiki/Tornikios\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Tornikios\">John Thornikos</a>, a retired general.  John served as the first abbot of Iviron. Died in 1002.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=John_the_Iberian&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-b-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-b_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">also known as <b>John the Georgian</b>, <b>John the <a href=\"/wiki/Hagiorite\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hagiorite\">Hagiorite</a></b>, and <b>John Iweron</b>.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Butler, p. 86</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Butler, p. 87</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Bibliography\">Bibliography</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=John_the_Iberian&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Bibliography\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Alban_Butler\" title=\"Alban Butler\">Butler, A.</a> (1995) Butler's Lives of the Saints, Volume 7, Liturgical Press</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=John_the_Iberian&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20071018002338/http://catholic-forum.com/saints/saintj7o.htm\">Saint John the Georgian</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.catholic.org/saints/saint.php?saint_id=4002\">St. John the Iberian</a></li></ul>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><span style=\"vertical-align: middle; background:transparent\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Flag_of_Georgia.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Flag of Georgia (country)\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0f/Flag_of_Georgia.svg/30px-Flag_of_Georgia.svg.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"30\" height=\"20\" class=\"thumbborder\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedi